    "body": "For finalised data, I think the key to this will be having a variable in finalised storage which records the hash of the not-yet-validated finalised transition block. If null either we've validated it or there isn't one (including it not being finalised yet).\n\nFor non-finalised we may already handle it but need to check - just need to pick up when we're switching the transition block from optimistic to valid and perform the check (if if we're doing that switch because a descendant was marked as valid).",
